S. E. J. COX v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 4431. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. Sept. 11, 1952. David Tant, Oklahoma City, Okl., for appellant. Whit Y. Mauzy, U. S. Atty., Tulsa, Old., for appellee.

Before PHILLIPS, Chief Judge, and MURRAH, Circuit Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed September 11, 1952, on motion of appellee, for failure of appellant diligently to prosecute.
